    **volumes**
*EC2 instances*
 Elastic block store
 volumes
create vol.
after that attach the vol. to the instance.

    **snapshots**
* open EC2 instances
   select the instance. (whose volume's snapshot to be taken)
   copy the volume id
 go to snapshots
    create snapshot
    name:   , paste the volume id
    create
 or go to volume > select vol. > actions > create snapshot from vol.
